Definition . "Confidential Materials" shall encompass, with reference to each party, any non-public written, electronic, or oral proprietary data transmitted, disclosed, or gained access to by the other party (or during their stay on the premises of either party) throughout the Term, in relation to this Agreement. This includes, but is not limited to, information regarding a party's products, services, designs, methodologies, business strategies, financial status, marketing initiatives, clientele or potential clients, and the specific terms of this Agreement. "Confidential Materials" shall exclude:

(a) Information that was known by the Receiving Party without a confidentiality obligation prior to its disclosure by the Disclosing Party;
(b) Information that is independently created by the Receiving Party;
(c) Information that becomes publicly accessible without a breach of this Agreement by the Receiving Party; or
(d) Information received from a third party who is under no obligation to preserve its confidentiality.

However, it is clarified that even if some portion of the Confidential Materials falls into one of the exceptions listed above, the Receiving Party shall still protect and maintain the confidentiality of any remaining portions that retain their confidential nature.
